#BLOCK: Pathfinder Delver Special Abilities
Master Explorer		KEY:Master Explorer ~ PaD		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DEFINE:PaDSkillBonus|0		SOURCEPAGE:p.58	DESC:You add %1 to all Disable Device and Perception checks. You can disable traps in half the normal amount of time (minimum 1 round) and open a lock as a standard action. You can always take 10 on Disable Device and Stealth checks. You can use Disable Device to disarm magical traps.|PaDSkillBonus																				BONUS:SKILL|Disable Device,Perception|PaDSkillBonus
Surefooted			KEY:Surefooted ~ PaD			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary						SOURCEPAGE:p.58	DESC:You can move through difficult terrain at your normal speed. Ground that has been magically manipulated to impeded motion still affects you normally.
Thrilling Escape		KEY:Thrilling Escape ~ PaD		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DEFINE:PaDEscapeTimes|0		SOURCEPAGE:p.58	DESC:You can attempt to delay a trap immediately after triggering it. You make a Disable Device check as an immediate action against the trap's Disable Device DC; if you are successful, the trap's activation is delayed until the end of your next turn. You can attempt this check even if the trap was triggered by a failed Disable Device check, or if it is not your turn. You can do this %1/day.|PaDEscapeTimes
Guardbreaker		KEY:Guardbreaker ~ PaD			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary						SOURCEPAGE:p.58	DESC:Your familiarity with the strange guardians often left in tombs allows you to attack them more effectively. You may treat your trap sense bonus as if it were a favored enemy bonus against constructs, oozes, and undead.																																BONUS:VAR|FavoredConstruct,FavoredOoze,FavoredUndead|TrapSenseBonus	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|PaDFE Construct|!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Favored Enemy (Construct)	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|PaDFE Ooze|!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Favored Enemy (Ooze)	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|PaDFE Undead|!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Favored Enemy (Undead)
Resourceful Disabler	KEY:Resourceful Disabler ~ PaD	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary						SOURCEPAGE:p.58	DESC:You are adept at making use of what's at hand. You can use the Disable Device skill without tools at no penalty.
Vigilant Combatant	KEY:Vigilant Combatant ~ PaD		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DEFINE:PaDInitiative|0		SOURCEPAGE:p.58	DESC:You add %1 to initiative checks.|PaDInitiative																																																													BONUS:COMBAT|Initiative|PaDInitiative
Left for Dead		KEY:Left for Dead ~ PaD			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural						SOURCEPAGE:p.58	DESC:1/day, you can cheat death. If you would be killed by a melee attack, ranged attack, or an effect that requires a saving throw, you are instead reduced to -1 hit points and knocked unconscious, but are stable. You appear dead, but become conscious 1 minute later unless awakened sooner.
Fortunate Soul		KEY:Fortunate Soul ~ PaD		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural	DEFINE:PaDFortunateTimes|0	SOURCEPAGE:p.58	DESC:You may reroll any saving throw you have just made before the results of the roll are revealed. You must take the result of the reroll, even if it's worse than the original roll. You may use this ability %1/day.|PaDFortunateTimes
True Seeing			KEY:True Seeing ~ PaD			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.SpellLike							SOURCEPAGE:p.58	DESC:You can use true seeing 1/day (caster level %1).|PaDTrueSeeingLvl																																																										SPELLS:Pathfinder Delver|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=PaDLvl|True Seeing,16+max(INT,WIS,CHA)
Nick of Time		KEY:Nick of Time ~ PaD			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary						SOURCEPAGE:p.58	DESC:You have a knack for choosing the best time to act. 1/day, you can use an immediate action to perform an action that normally requires a standard action to perform.

